{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0655fa0723b52fadd2169a4fd6b3589f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nThe LLM verifier intentionally uses `bare` (no-tools) mode for two reasons:\n\n**1. Prevent evidence fabrication**\n\nThe verifier prompt (`src/cluster.ts:481-495`) explicitly instructs:\n> \"Do not infer. Do not use tools. Return JSON only.\"\n\nRunning with `agent` mode would allow the verifier Claude process to invoke `Agent`, `Glob`, or `Read` — it could discover evidence that wasn't in the original factsheet and incorrectly mark facts as `VERIFIED`. The verifier would be generating evidence, not checking it.\n\n**2. Measured cost efficiency**\n\nFrom the experiments in `docs/CLUSTER_CACHE_SPEC.md:19-21`:\n\n| Mode | Duration | Input Tokens |\n|------|----------|-------------|\n| `Agent` + `Glob` + `Read` (exploration) | 264.8s | 56,051 |\n| `--bare --tools \"\"` (verified factsheet) | 36.8s | 1,170 |\n\nThe `bare` profile is ~22x cheaper in tokens and ~7x faster for this use case. Verification only needs to read pre-cited evidence strings — it doesn't need tool access.\n\n**3. Verifier prompt is injected via `profilePromptOptions`**\n\nAt `src/cluster.ts:369`:\n\n```ts\nawait claude.runPromptWithOptions(prompt, profilePromptOptions(toolProfile))\n```\n\nFor `bare`, `profilePromptOptions` produces `extraArgs: [\"--bare\", \"--tools\", \"\"]`. For `focused`, it produces `extraArgs: [\"--tools\", \"\"]`. Neither enables `Agent`/`Glob`/`Read`, ensuring the verification verdict is based purely on the submitted evidence strings, not on self-discovered补充内容."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":111816,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","uuid":"c9bc674d-2fab-4fd8-b105-41a644699954"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":7048,"duration_api_ms":7002,"num_turns":1,"result":"\n\n\nThe LLM verifier intentionally uses `bare` (no-tools) mode for two reasons:\n\n**1. Prevent evidence fabrication**\n\nThe verifier prompt (`src/cluster.ts:481-495`) explicitly instructs:\n> \"Do not infer. Do not use tools. Return JSON only.\"\n\nRunning with `agent` mode would allow the verifier Claude process to invoke `Agent`, `Glob`, or `Read` — it could discover evidence that wasn't in the original factsheet and incorrectly mark facts as `VERIFIED`. The verifier would be generating evidence, not checking it.\n\n**2. Measured cost efficiency**\n\nFrom the experiments in `docs/CLUSTER_CACHE_SPEC.md:19-21`:\n\n| Mode | Duration | Input Tokens |\n|------|----------|-------------|\n| `Agent` + `Glob` + `Read` (exploration) | 264.8s | 56,051 |\n| `--bare --tools \"\"` (verified factsheet) | 36.8s | 1,170 |\n\nThe `bare` profile is ~22x cheaper in tokens and ~7x faster for this use case. Verification only needs to read pre-cited evidence strings — it doesn't need tool access.\n\n**3. Verifier prompt is injected via `profilePromptOptions`**\n\nAt `src/cluster.ts:369`:\n\n```ts\nawait claude.runPromptWithOptions(prompt, profilePromptOptions(toolProfile))\n```\n\nFor `bare`, `profilePromptOptions` produces `extraArgs: [\"--bare\", \"--tools\", \"\"]`. For `focused`, it produces `extraArgs: [\"--tools\", \"\"]`. Neither enables `Agent`/`Glob`/`Read`, ensuring the verification verdict is based purely on the submitted evidence strings, not on self-discovered补充内容.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","total_cost_usd":0.07818,"usage":{"input_tokens":2528,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":111680,"output_tokens":388,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"infe